            </p>
          </div>
          
          <div class="bg-white rounded-lg shadow-md p-6">
            <h3 class="text-xl font-semibold mb-3">How often should I visit a hair dresser?</h3>
            <p class="text-gray-700">
              Most people should visit a hair dresser every 6-8 weeks for maintenance. However, this varies based on several factors: hair growth rate, style complexity, and whether you have color treatments. Color touch-ups typically need attention every 4-6 weeks, while some low-maintenance styles can go 10-12 weeks between visits.
            </p>
          </div>
          
          <div class="bg-white rounded-lg shadow-md p-6">
            <h3 class="text-xl font-semibold mb-3">What's the difference between hair dressing and hair styling?</h3>
            <p class="text-gray-700">
              Hair dressing is the broader profession encompassing cutting, coloring, chemical treatments, and overall hair care. Hair styling specifically refers to arranging hair into a particular look using tools and products. While all hair dressers can style hair, hair dressing includes the technical skills of cutting and coloring that require professional licensing.
            </p>
          </div>
          
          <div class="bg-white rounded-lg shadow-md p-6">
            <h3 class="text-xl font-semibold mb-3">How do I choose the right hair dresser?</h3>
            <p class="text-gray-700">
              Look for a hair dresser with proper qualifications, experience in your desired services, and a portfolio that matches your style preferences. Read reviews, ask for consultations, and ensure they listen to your needs. A good hair dresser will consider your lifestyle, maintenance preferences, and hair type when recommending styles.
            </p>
          </div>
          
          <div class="bg-white rounded-lg shadow-md p-6">
            <h3 class="text-xl font-semibold mb-3">What should I expect during a hair dressing appointment?</h3>
            <p class="text-gray-700">
              A professional appointment begins with a consultation to discuss your goals and assess your hair. The hair dresser will recommend suitable options, explain the process, and provide pricing. Services typically include shampooing, the main service (cut/color/treatment), styling, and home care advice. Quality salons also offer refreshments and a relaxing atmosphere.
            </p>
          </div>
        </div>
